</form>
6. What is the difference between localStorage, sessionStorage, and cookies in HTML5?

âœ… Answer:
	â€¢	localStorage:
	â€¢	Stores data permanently (until cleared).
	â€¢	5â€“10 MB capacity.
	â€¢	sessionStorage:
	â€¢	Stores data for a session (clears on tab close).
	â€¢	5â€“10 MB capacity.
	â€¢	Cookies:
	â€¢	Small (4 KB).
	â€¢	Sent to the server with each request â†’ network overhead.
	â€¢	Used for authentication/session tracking.

ğŸ‘‰ Example:
