8. What is the difference between block, inline, and inline-block elements?

âœ… Answer:
	â€¢	Block: Takes full width, starts new line (<div>, <section>).
	â€¢	Inline: Takes only content width, does not start new line (<span>, <a>).
	â€¢	Inline-block: Behaves like inline, but allows block properties (<button>, <img>).

